The improper installation of the generator can cause it to shut off automatically without warning, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing a fire due to the exhaust pipe being aligned with the gas line.
symptoms: The generator shuts off automatically after 30 minutes of operation
the generator fails to provide power
the air conditioning system fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor design of the motorhome can cause difficulties for the driver, including unreachable switches, lack of resistance in the steering, and excessive movement of the slide-outs in windy conditions, which can lead to accidents or make the vehicle difficult to control.
symptoms: the slide-outs move excessively in windy conditions
the vehicle wanders all over the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fractured Fuel Tank Cross-Member and Filler Spout
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fractured fuel tank cross-member and filler spout can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and serious accidents.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor after filling the tank
fuel leaking from the filler spout
fractured or compressed filler spout against the fuel tank.
